<div id="definite_window" style="display: none;">
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">PO = Purchase Order (customer's purchase authorization to seller)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">Inv = Invoice (seller's invoice to customers)</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">All Income (includes NYD, DEP, NYA, and APP income below)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">NYD = Income not yet Deposited (seller has received income but has not deposited)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">DEP = Deposit (customer deposited payment in bank account)</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">NYA = Not Yet Applied (seller has received the payment but has not yet used it to cancel the charges for the invoices that were paid off by this payment. Check or ACH info will normally specify which invoices a payment applies to).</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">APP = Income Applied to All Invoices (income has been fully applied to invoices)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">PAR = Income Applied to Some Invoices (Partial Payment)</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">Income Tax Required Classifications for the Sale of Merchandise</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">IS = In State (customer is inside Washington State ... not Washington, DC)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">OS = Out of State (customer is outside of Washington State)</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">x</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">WS = Wholesale (customer is a bookstore that will resell the product)</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">RT = Retail (customer is the end user. He/she will not resell the product)</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">OS/WS = Out of State / Wholesale</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">IS/WS = In State / Wholesale</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-0">OS/RT = Out of State / Retail</p>
    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">IS/RT = In State / Retail</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">Income from Fees (Editing, etc), Rights Sale, or Grant do NOT need to be broken down according the 4 categories above.</p>

    <p class="font-14 font-weight-bold mb-3">CTR (Ch To Roy) = Change to Royalities (this income has been used to calcuate Author Royalities)</p>
</div>

